{
  "stem": "18581.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Vilna before 1939 belonged to Poland, so these people wanted to leave the Soviet Union, so they wanted to repatriate to Poland.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And for that they needed to document that they were not essential, their work was not essential for-- for the Ministry, so I gave them such documents.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The last document I gave was to Mrs.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Yoffe and to her little girl, who is now married in-- somewhere in New York.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Mrs.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yoffe, Y-O-F-F-E, and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] her daughter Esti.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I believe-- I believe it was Esti, E-S-T-I.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] She worked-- they both worked for me, for us, for the Ministry.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I gave them the document.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then I disappeared myself.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And in three days, we all were on a truck that we rented.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they took us not on the highway, but on byways, to avoid-- to avoid the border, because although Poland-- the free Poland was, so to speak, a-- still under the Soviets, but it was different from the Soviet Union.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I guess in-- in July.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1945.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "One year.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What-- when the Germans--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 70,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In May, in May of '45.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 71,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, everybody was happy that the Germans lost the war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I-- I frankly was more worried to get out.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What-- because Lithuanian Jews were in a predicament.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 72,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They couldn't get out like others, like Polish refugees Jews.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 73,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Or just from Vilna, because we were made Soviet citizens again.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 74,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I decided the moment I came, in July '43-- '44, excuse me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 75,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--when I--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Where did I go?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I went to Bialystock, B-I-A-L-Y-S-T-O-K.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And from Bialystok, we went to Lodz, L-O-D-Z.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And from there, we had already contact with the Berihah, with the-- with the Jewish underground that originated in Palestine.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They-- they helped us.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
